epicene (EP-i-seen) adjective

   1. Having characteristics of both sexes.

   2. Effeminate.

noun

   A person or object that is epicene.

[From Middle English, from Latin epicoenus, from Greek epikoinos, epi- +
koinos, common.]

WordPix: http://wordsmith.org/words/epicene.gif

   "`This time I've bought an epicene sweater so either of us can wear it!'
   Mrs. Fraugal chirped as she showed her husband the bright pink dress."

This week's theme: WordPix, words drawn so that they explain themselves.

